WEBVTT

00:00.750 --> 00:02.229
- HOW'D YOU GET THAT INTERVIEW?

00:02.340 --> 00:03.784
- CARL, WHO YOU MET
THE OTHER NIGHT.

00:03.900 --> 00:05.026
- HEY, HANK.
- SO I WONDER

00:05.140 --> 00:05.959
IF WE COULD
DO THE JOB TOGETHER.

00:06.070 --> 00:07.378
- JUST LIKE WE USED TO.

00:07.490 --> 00:07.899
- EXCEPT THAT I'M THE BOSS.

00:08.000 --> 00:09.865
- [chuckles]

00:09.970 --> 00:11.346
- YOUR GIRLFRIEND
HASN'T TOLD HER PARENTS

00:11.450 --> 00:13.657
THAT SHE DIDN'T
GO BACK TO TUFI'S?

00:13.770 --> 00:14.316
IT'S BEEN TWO WEEKS.

00:14.420 --> 00:15.660
HOW LONG IS SHE GONNA STAY?

00:15.770 --> 00:20.594
- IF SELLING THIS HOUSE
IS IMPORTANT TO YOU

00:20.710 --> 00:21.563
THEN I'M WILLING TO DO THAT,

00:21.670 --> 00:24.116
BECAUSE BEING IN THIS HOUSE
WITHOUT YOU

00:24.230 --> 00:26.539
IS JUST NOT GONNA WORK.

00:26.640 --> 00:28.574
- I'M MOVING OUT, JULIA.

00:28.680 --> 00:30.819
- NO, YOU CAN'T DO THIS.
WE'RE A FAMILY.

00:30.920 --> 00:32.603
YOU CAN'T GO!

00:34.580 --> 00:37.231
- MM. OKAY, PACK UP
THOSE BACKPACKS.

00:37.340 --> 00:41.822
DAD IS GONNA BE HERE ANY MINUTE
AND...I GOT THESE FOR YOU.

00:41.930 --> 00:43.966
BLUE FOR VICTOR...
- COOL.

00:44.070 --> 00:47.107
- AND RED FOR SYDNEY.
- WHY'S IT SO HEAW?

00:47.210 --> 00:50.759
- BECAUSE I PACKED EVERYTHING I
THOUGHT YOU COULD POSSIBLY NEED

00:50.870 --> 00:51.973
FOR YOUR BIG WEEKEND WITH DAD.

00:52.080 --> 00:52.830
- SO WE HAVE TO CARRY
THESE AROUND ALL DAY?

00:52.940 --> 00:53.838
WE ALREADY HAVE BACKPACKS.

00:53.950 --> 00:54.974
- NO, THEY'RE FOR DAD.

00:55.080 --> 00:56.900
HE'S GONNA TAKE THEM
TO HIS APARTMENT

00:57.020 --> 00:58.328
AFI'ER HE DROPS YOU OFF
AT SCHOOL, 50--

00:58.430 --> 01:00.318
- IT'S JUST A BAG.
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

01:00.430 --> 01:01.499
- THANK YOU.
- OH, GOD.

01:08.890 --> 01:11.541
- HEY!
- DAD.

01:11.650 --> 01:12.639
- THERE'S MY MAN.

01:12.760 --> 01:13.715
HEY, BUDDY.

01:13.830 --> 01:14.717
YOU NEED HELP WITH THIS?

01:14.830 --> 01:15.649
- NO, IT'S OKAY.
- OKAY.

01:15.760 --> 01:17.614
- I CALL SHOTGUN!
both: NO, NO SHOTGUN.

01:17.730 --> 01:18.936
- YOU'RE GONNA SIT IN THE BACK
WITH YOUR SISTER.

01:19.040 --> 01:20.484
IT'S SAFER.

01:20.590 --> 01:22.069
IS THIS--IS THIS EVERYTHING?
- YEAH.

01:22.180 --> 01:25.559
- OH, OKAY.
- SO, UH...

01:25.670 --> 01:27.729
I GUESS--
- HAVE A GOOD WEEKEND.

01:27.840 --> 01:29.705
- YEAH, YOU TOO.
- OKAY.

01:32.230 --> 01:34.152
- ALL RIGHT, GUYS.
- ALL RIGHT, YOU GUYS.

01:34.260 --> 01:36.433
- SEE YOU SUNDAY.

01:36.540 --> 01:38.155
BYE.
BYE.

01:38.270 --> 01:39.988
- WHO IS HUNGRY?
Victor: I'M HUNGRY.

01:40.100 --> 01:41.169
- I FIGURED.

01:41.270 --> 01:41.816
[doorbell rings]

01:46.140 --> 01:47.334
- HEY.
- OH, HI.

01:47.450 --> 01:48.997
- HOW ARE YA?
- UM, IS ZEEK HERE OR CAMILLE?

01:49.100 --> 01:51.068
- UH, THEY'RE BOTH OUT.

01:51.180 --> 01:52.340
THOSE ARE MY FOLKS.
- OKAY.

01:52.450 --> 01:53.656
I'M THEIR REAL ESTATE AGENT,
KAREN.

01:53.760 --> 01:54.966
I'M JUST GONNA DROP THESE OFF
WITH YOU RIGHT NOW.

01:55.080 --> 01:58.629
THEY'RE THE COMPS THEY WANTED TO
SEE BEFORE WE OFFICIALLY LIST.

01:58.730 --> 02:00.482
- LIST?

02:00.600 --> 02:02.386
- THIS HOUSE.
- LIST--LIST THIS HOUSE?

02:02.500 --> 02:03.694
- THIS HOUSE, YEAH.
- FOR SALE?

02:03.810 --> 02:05.038
- UH-HUH, FOR SALE
WITH MULTIPLE OFFERS.

02:05.150 --> 02:06.014
FINGERS CROSSED.
[phone rings]

02:06.120 --> 02:07.599
OOH, SORRY, GOTTA GET THIS.

02:07.710 --> 02:08.631
- OKAY.
- THANKS.

02:08.740 --> 02:10.184
EXCUSE ME.
- YOU BET.

02:15.130 --> 02:18.509
- WOW, COULD YOUR FIRST CLASS
BE ANY FARTHER FROM YOUR DORM?

02:18.620 --> 02:20.269
- YEAH, WELL,
YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO COME.

02:20.380 --> 02:22.541
YOU KNOW, I KNOW HOW TO GET TO
THIS CLASS AT THIS POINT.

02:22.650 --> 02:24.993
- I'M JUST SAYING
IT'S WAY BIGGER THAN TUFI'S.

02:25.110 --> 02:28.102
AND THE WEATHER'S NICER,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

02:28.210 --> 02:31.008
- UM, WELL, I ACT UALLY--
I HAVE A LAB AFTER THIS.

02:31.110 --> 02:34.216
- YEAH, YEAH.
ASTRONOMY, I KNOW.

02:34.320 --> 02:36.140
- WELL, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

02:36.250 --> 02:37.945
- I'LL PROBABLY JUST
GO TO THE STUDENT CENTER,

02:38.050 --> 02:39.142
GRAB SOME COFFEE OR SOMETHING.

02:39.260 --> 02:40.397
DO YOU WANT ME
TO GRAB YOU ANYTHING?

02:40.500 --> 02:43.014
- UH, NO, I'M GOOD.
- OKAY.

02:43.120 --> 02:44.985
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
I WILL MEET YOU BACK HERE?

02:45.090 --> 02:47.467
- UM, YEAH, SURE.
- OKAY.

02:49.300 --> 02:50.676
- OKAY, HERE WE ARE.

02:50.790 --> 02:52.121
NOW, YOU GUYS
ARE SHARING A ROOM,

02:52.240 --> 02:54.811
BUT I GOT YQU BUNK BEDS.
[humming n0|se]

02:54.930 --> 02:57.091
YOU GUYS GOTTA SEE IT.
THEY'RE LIKE A FORT.

02:57.210 --> 02:59.166
HERE WE GO.
- WHAT'S THAT HUMMING?

02:59.280 --> 03:00.827
- SOUNDS LIKE THE ELEVATOR.

03:00.930 --> 03:03.581
- UH, YEAH, YOU CAN'T HEAR IT
FROM THE BEDROOM THOUGH.

03:03.700 --> 03:05.964
HERE WE GO.
SO HERE IS THE LIVING ROOM.

03:06.080 --> 03:09.311
WE GOT THE KITCHEN OVER THERE.
DINING ROOM OVER HERE.

03:09.430 --> 03:12.183
THIS TV SCREEN, NO JOKE,
PLAYS 3-D MOVIES.

03:12.290 --> 03:13.666
- COOL.
- THEN RIGHT DOWN HERE,

03:13.770 --> 03:15.567
WE GOT OUR OLD TRUSTY FRIEND.
- YOU HAVE AN XBOX?

03:15.670 --> 03:16.944
- AN XBOX.
WE GOT CABLE.

03:17.050 --> 03:20.508
WE GOT PRETTY MUCH EVERYTHING
WE HAVE AT HO--AT THE HOUSE.

03:20.610 --> 03:22.293
CHECK IT OUT.
I GOT A COUPLE OF GAMES

03:22.400 --> 03:23.913
WE COULD TRY OUT THIS WEEKEND.
- COOL.

03:24.030 --> 03:26.476
- SYD. HERE'S THAT
RAINBOW LOOM YOU HAVE AT HOME.

03:26.580 --> 03:28.093
I THOUGHT WE COULD,
UH, YOU KNOW,

03:28.200 --> 03:31.545
GO RAINBOW...BRACELET CRAZY
THIS WEEKEND.

03:31.650 --> 03:33.789
- I DON'T PLAY
WITH THAT ANYMORE.

03:33.900 --> 03:35.925
I'M TEN NOW.

03:36.040 --> 03:37.177
- YOU DON'T?

03:37.280 --> 03:39.965
OKAY, WELL, UH,
MAYBE WE'LL JUST HAVE TO

03:40.080 --> 03:42.105
GO TO THE TOY STORE AND
FIND SOMETHING YOU DO PLAY WITH.

03:42.220 --> 03:43.869
HEY, ONE LAST THING.

03:48.780 --> 03:51.635
- THERE'S A POOL?
- THERE IS A POOL, YES.

03:51.740 --> 03:53.367
- SO WE CAN GO SWIMMING?
- YEAH, WE COULD PROBABLY

03:53.470 --> 03:55.222
SQUEEZE IN A QUICK SWIM
BEFORE DINNER.

03:55.330 --> 03:57.605
- BUT WE DIDN'T BRING
OUR BATHING SUITS.

03:57.720 --> 03:59.472
- WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING DAD
BOUGHT YOU BATHING SUITS

03:59.580 --> 04:00.194
AND PUT 'EM ON YOUR BED.

04:00.300 --> 04:03.019
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO, GO.

04:03.130 --> 04:05.826
SECOND DOOR ON THE LEFT.

04:14.530 --> 04:17.078
MAY GOD BLESS
AND KEEP YOU ALWAYS

04:17.180 --> 04:19.740
AND MAY YOUR WISHES
ALL COME TRUE

04:19.840 --> 04:22.047
MAY YOU ALWAYS DO
FOR OTHERS

04:22.150 --> 04:24.493
AND LET OTHERS DO FOR YOU

04:24.600 --> 04:27.046
MAY YOU BUILD A LADDER
TO THE STARS

04:27.160 --> 04:29.219
AND CLIMB ON EVERY RUNG

04:29.330 --> 04:31.707
AND MAY YOU STAY

04:31.820 --> 04:34.095
FOREVER YOUNG

04:34.200 --> 04:36.953
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE RIGHTEOUS

04:37.060 --> 04:38.197
MAY YOU GROW UP
TO BE TRUE

04:38.310 --> 04:41.541
MAY YOU ALWAYS KNOW
THE TRUTH

04:41.660 --> 04:43.753
AND SEE THE LIGHTS
SURROUNDING YOU

04:43.860 --> 04:46.556
MAY YOU ALWAYS BE
COURAGEOUS

04:46.660 --> 04:48.833
STAND UPRIGHT
AND BE STRONG

04:48.940 --> 04:50.794
AND MAY YOU STAY

04:50.910 --> 04:53.310
FOREVER YOUNG

04:53.430 --> 04:55.762
MAY YOU STAY

04:55.880 --> 04:58.565
FOREVER YOUNG

05:02.020 --> 05:04.159
- MM.

05:04.260 --> 05:05.818
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE JUST GOT IN THE CAR

05:05.920 --> 05:07.194
AND DROVE TO MENDOCINO.

05:07.300 --> 05:09.746
THAT'S SO CRAZY OF US.

05:09.860 --> 05:12.818
- SCANDALOUS.
- I KNOW! CRAZY CRAZY.

05:12.930 --> 05:14.716
- WHO DO WE HAVE TO THANK
FOR THIS TRIP AGAIN?

05:14.830 --> 05:17.162
- PHIL AND SUE GAVE US
THE GIFT CERTIFICATE.

05:17.280 --> 05:18.588
- THE LESSINGS? REALLY?
- NICE, RIGHT?

05:18.690 --> 05:20.510
I KNOW, IT'S SO WEIRD THOUGH.

05:20.630 --> 05:22.860
PEOPLE GIVING YOU GIFTS
BECAUSE YOU HAVE CANCER.

05:22.970 --> 05:25.552
OH, IT'S NICE THOUGH.
- IT IS WEIRD.

05:25.670 --> 05:27.479
- BUT IT IS RELAXING.

05:27.600 --> 05:30.216
YOU RELAXING?
- YUP.

05:30.330 --> 05:33.049
- YEAH?

05:35.540 --> 05:37.986
- I GOTTA MAKE A QUICK
PHONE CALL, ALL RIGHT?

05:38.090 --> 05:40.012
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
- TO WHO?

05:40.130 --> 05:41.461
- IT'S JUST A WORK THING
I FORGOT.

05:41.580 --> 05:43.298
GOTTA GET IT OFF MY MIND.
- OKAY.

05:43.410 --> 05:45.640
[YEIPS]
OH! OH, MY GOD!

05:45.750 --> 05:47.889
THAT COLD MOUNTAIN AIR!

05:50.970 --> 05:52.858
[phone rings]

05:52.970 --> 05:54.346
- HELLO?

05:54.450 --> 05:55.929
- HEY, JULES,
IT'S YOUR BIG BROTHER.

05:56.040 --> 05:59.521
- YOU ARE NOT CALLING ME FROM
YOUR SPA WEEKEND IN MENDOCINO.

05:59.630 --> 06:01.359
- LISTEN, I JUST HAD TO
CALL AND CHECK UP.

06:01.460 --> 06:03.519
I WAS WORRIED ABOUT YOU.
HOW YOU DOING?

06:03.630 --> 06:05.382
- UH, I'M--I'M FINE.
- YOU SURE?

06:05.500 --> 06:07.639
- ADAM, THANK YOU SO MUCH,

06:07.740 --> 06:09.253
BUT I'M--I'M F--DON'T WORRY
ABOUT ME, OKAY?

06:09.360 --> 06:11.499
TRULY, I'VE GOT
A WHOLE SCHEDULE.

06:11.610 --> 06:14.841
I ALREADY MADE A TARGET RUN,
I CLEANED OUT THE FREEZER,

06:14.960 --> 06:16.291
I DID AN EXPIRATION DATE PURGE
IN THE PANTRY,

06:16.410 --> 06:19.959
AND NOW I'M ABOUT TO BINGE WATCH
ORANGE IS THE NEW BLACK,SO...

06:20.060 --> 06:23.439
- ALL RIGHT, WELL, THAT SOUNDS,
UH, PRODUCTIVE, I GUESS.

06:23.550 --> 06:28.442
- YEAH, WELL, YOU JUST WORRY
ABOUT SHOWING KRISTINA

06:28.560 --> 06:29.686
A GOOD TIME AND TELL ME
YOU'RE NOT WEARING

06:29.800 --> 06:31.825
THAT OLD MAN BATHING SUIT
OF YOURS.

06:31.940 --> 06:33.146
- THESE ARE MY TRUNKS!
- I'LL TAKE THAT AS A YES.

06:33.250 --> 06:35.309
- I'VE HAD THESE TRUNKS FOREVER.
I LOVE MY TRUNKS!

06:35.420 --> 06:37.388
DON'T BE DISSIN' MY TRUNKS.

06:37.500 --> 06:39.115
- OKAY.
I'M HANGING UP NOW.

06:39.220 --> 06:40.494
BYE.
- ALL RIGHT, I LOVE YOU.

06:43.400 --> 06:46.631
HONEY?

06:46.750 --> 06:50.083
[YEIPS]
OH, HO HO HO, IT'S COLD!

06:50.200 --> 06:53.499
- YOU'RE A WUSS.
- OH! WHAT?

06:54.930 --> 06:56.443
- YOU'RE SO WEIRD!

06:56.550 --> 06:57.448
- I JUST NEED YOU
TO CLOSE YOUR EYES, OKAY?

06:57.550 --> 06:59.654
- ALL RIGHT.
- JUST CLOSE YOUR EYES.

06:59.760 --> 07:01.921
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO THINK ABOUT A THING.

07:02.040 --> 07:04.508
YOU'RE GOOD.
YOU'RE ALL GOOD, OKAY?

07:04.630 --> 07:07.246
AH, ALL RIGHT, YOU CAN OPEN 'EM.
- [laughs]

07:07.350 --> 07:08.624
ARE YOU LOSIN' THE TRUNKS?

07:08.730 --> 07:10.072
- TIME TO SAY GOOD-BYE.
- YEAH.

07:10.180 --> 07:11.522
- OKAY?
- I LOVE IT!

07:15.950 --> 07:18.259
- SOME OF THESE ARE PRETTY GOOD.

07:18.360 --> 07:20.225
- "SOME OF THESE
ARE PRETTY GOOD."

07:20.330 --> 07:21.319
A RAVE.

07:21.440 --> 07:22.771
- WELL, NOT THESE.

07:22.890 --> 07:24.152
- NO?
- UNUSABLE, UNUSABLE.

07:24.270 --> 07:26.295
- THEY'RE NOT UNUSABLE.
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

07:26.410 --> 07:27.604
THOSE ARE MY FAVORITE ONES.

07:27.720 --> 07:29.119
- TACO TRUCK
IN THE BACKGROUND RUINS IT.

07:29.240 --> 07:31.094
- IT DOESN'T RUIN IT.
THE TACO TRUCK WAS THE POINT.

07:31.200 --> 07:32.201
I PUT IT THERE.

07:32.310 --> 07:33.618
- WE COULD TAKE IT OUT LATER.
- DON'T TAKE IT OUT.

07:33.720 --> 07:35.472
- IT DRAWS YOUR EYE FROM
THE SURFERS AND SURFBOARD,

07:35.590 --> 07:37.376
AND THAT'S--THIS IS
A SURFSPORT SHOOT, RIGHT?

07:37.490 --> 07:39.629
- NO, IT--
- so—-so—-

07:39.730 --> 07:41.413
- OKAY.
- I WOULD SAY...SCRATCH THOSE.

07:41.530 --> 07:42.599
- SLEEP ON IT, WOULD YOU?

07:42.700 --> 07:43.837
JUST LOOK AT THOSE AGAIN
TOMORROW?

07:43.940 --> 07:45.248
- I DON'T NEED TO
SLEEP ON THAT.

07:45.360 --> 07:46.622
I ALREADY KNOW
THOSE ARE NO GOOD.

07:46.740 --> 07:47.593
- THAT WAS PART
OF MY WHOLE VISION.

07:47.700 --> 07:48.689
THOSE ARE MY FAVORITE ONES.

07:48.810 --> 07:51.119
- YEAH, WELL, VISION?
I MEAN--

07:51.220 --> 07:52.460
- DON'T LAUGH WHEN I SAY VISION.
- SOME OF THEM ARE GOOD.

07:52.570 --> 07:54.845
I SAID SOME OF 'EM ARE GOOD.
- I GOTTA GO.

07:54.950 --> 07:56.087
THANK YOU.
I WILL LIVE ON THAT.

07:56.190 --> 07:57.919
I'LL DINE OUT ON THAT
FOR THE NEXT THREE YEARS.

07:58.020 --> 07:59.499
- WHAT DO YOU GOT, BIG DATE?
- WHAT?

07:59.610 --> 08:01.430
- LIPSTICK AND ALL?
- YES, I'M GOING TO DINNER,

08:01.550 --> 08:04.098
BUT I'M NOT--
IT'S NOT A BIG DATE.

08:04.200 --> 08:05.064
I'M MEETING CARL FOR DINNER.

08:05.170 --> 08:07.889
- SO IT'S KINDA
TURNING INTO SOMETHING?

08:08.000 --> 08:09.308
- WITH CARL? NO.
- THAT'S GOOD.

08:09.410 --> 08:10.729
- WHY IS THAT--WHY?

08:10.830 --> 08:13.139
WHAT DO YOU MEAN? NO.
HE'S A NEIGHBOR.

08:13.250 --> 08:14.444
I'M MEETING HIM FOR DINNER.

08:14.560 --> 08:16.141
- WITH LIPSTICK TOO?

08:16.250 --> 08:18.138
DO YOU EAT--HOW'S THAT WORK?
- I'VE WORN LIPSTICK BEFORE.

08:18.250 --> 08:20.047
I WEAR IT FREQUENTLY.
- YOU GOTTA DRINK WITH A STRAW,

08:20.150 --> 08:22.004
RIGHT, 'CAUSE YOU'RE GONNA
GET IT ON THE GLASS?

08:22.120 --> 08:23.144
THAT'S NOT ATTRACTIVE.

08:23.260 --> 08:24.704
IS IT MAUVE?
- IT'S NOT MAUVE.

08:24.810 --> 08:25.731
I GOTTA GO.
- YEAH.

08:25.850 --> 08:27.533
HAVE A GOOD TIME.
- OKAY, THANKS.

08:27.640 --> 08:29.949
- ALL RIGHT.
IT'S A GOOD COLOR THOUGH.

08:30.060 --> 08:33.951
IT'LL LOOK GOOD WHEN IT'S ON
THE VEAL PARMIGIANA OR WHATEVER.

08:42.830 --> 08:45.549
- HEY.

08:45.660 --> 08:47.935
- HEY, DREW.

08:48.040 --> 08:49.268
- WELL, YEAH.
- [glggleSI

08:49.390 --> 08:51.529
- LATER.

08:51.630 --> 08:54.178
- SO IS SHE, LIKE,
LIVING HERE NOW?

08:54.290 --> 08:55.382
- WHO?

08:55.500 --> 08:56.831
- WHO DO YOU THINK? AMY.
- OH, AMY?

08:56.950 --> 08:58.497
- YEAH, AMY.
- NO. SHE'S JUST BEEN--

08:58.600 --> 09:00.704
SHE'S STAYING HERE
FOR A COUPLE OF WEEKS.

09:00.810 --> 09:01.708
- I'M FINE WITH IT.
I MEAN, WHATEVER,

09:01.810 --> 09:04.392
THE FACT THAT
YOU'RE BLOWING ME OFF,

09:04.500 --> 09:07.776
BUT IT'S LIKE
SHE'S JUST ALWAYS AROUND.

09:07.890 --> 09:10.643
SHE, LIKE, WAITS FOR YOU
OUTSIDE OF CLASS

09:10.750 --> 09:12.684
TO PICK YOU UP AND--LOOK,
EVERY SINGLE TIME YOU TALK TO ME

09:12.790 --> 09:14.781
YOU'RE LOOKING AROUND
LIKE YOU DON'T WANT HER

09:14.890 --> 09:16.130
TO SEE US TOGETHER.
- OH, MY GOSH.

09:16.240 --> 09:19.107
- WHAT IS THAT? IT'S JUST--
IT'S WEIRD, THAT'S ALL.

09:19.210 --> 09:20.438
HEY, AMY.

09:20.560 --> 09:23.063
- HEY.
- HEY.

09:23.180 --> 09:26.343
- JUST LET ME KNOW IF YOU WANNA
COME BACK TO THE WORLD.

09:26.460 --> 09:29.315
- HEY.
- HEY. IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

09:30.390 --> 09:31.209
- NORA.
NORA.

09:31.320 --> 09:33.072
STOP.
STOP.

09:33.190 --> 09:34.634
- LOOK, SHE NEEDS
A SPOON TO EAT.

09:34.740 --> 09:35.320
- NO, SHE DOESN'T.
SHE USES HER FINGERS AT HOME.

09:35.430 --> 09:36.328
- I KINDA LIKED IT.

09:36.430 --> 09:38.807
SHE HAS A LOT OF RHYTHM.

09:38.920 --> 09:40.399
- THIS MILK TASTES FUNNY.
- IT DOES?

09:40.510 --> 09:41.260
- IT'S THE SAME MILK
WE USE AT HOME.

09:41.370 --> 09:43.429
- CAN I HAVE WATER INSTEAD?

09:43.540 --> 09:45.360
- ME TOO.
- OH, NOW YOU WANT WATER?

09:45.480 --> 09:46.708
EVERYONE'S TOO GOOD FOR MILK?

09:46.820 --> 09:48.640
- WOW, HAVE THOSE THINGS
COME A LONG WAY.

09:48.760 --> 09:51.069
SINCE BACK IN THE DAY.
YEAH, WHEN CROSBY WAS A BABY

09:51.170 --> 09:53.650
HE HAD TO SCREAM HIS LUNGS OUT
BEFORE WE EVER HEARD HIM.

09:53.760 --> 09:55.239
POOR THING.
- YOU KNOW SOMETHING, JABBAR?

09:55.350 --> 09:56.442
YOUR DAD HAD THE LOUDEST LUNGS

09:56.560 --> 09:58.448
I'VE EVER HEARD IN MY LIFE.
[laughter]

09:58.560 --> 10:00.619
- EXPLAINS A LOT.
[baby monitor feedback]

10:00.730 --> 10:02.004
- I WAS ALWAYS FEARLESS
AND BRAVE.

10:02.110 --> 10:02.667
- THIS THING'S MAKING
TOO MUCH STATIC.

10:02.770 --> 10:04.112
IT'S HURTING MY EARS.

10:04.220 --> 10:07.667
- WELL, LET ME FIX THAT FOR YOU,
YOUNG SQUIRE.

10:07.770 --> 10:09.635
[static gone]
THAT BETTER, MAX?

10:09.740 --> 10:11.913
- IS THAT ALL YOU'RE EATING?
- OH, YEAH.

10:12.020 --> 10:13.567
- I THINK YOU SHOULD HAVE
A LITTLE SOMETHING ELSE.

