33:21.100 --> 33:22.408
- IT'S HARD BEING
MR. PERFECT PANTS.

33:22.510 --> 33:23.920
- HOW MANY BOTTLES OF WINE AWAY
ARE WE HERE ANYWAY?

33:24.030 --> 33:25.201
- OH!
- WHO'S COUNTING?

33:25.310 --> 33:26.618
- THE--THE AUDITOR'S HERE.

33:26.720 --> 33:28.540
- I MIGHT HAVE TO TRY AND PLAY
A LITTLE CATCH-UP HERE.

33:28.660 --> 33:29.820
- THAT'S THE SPIRIT.
- WHAT ARE WE HAVING?

33:29.930 --> 33:30.897
- OH, BOY.
- ARE YOU HUNGRY?

33:31.000 --> 33:32.968
WE HAVE FOOD.
WE HAVE SO MUCH FOOD LEFT.

33:33.080 --> 33:35.002
- A LITTLE MALBEC.
IS THIS IT?

33:35.110 --> 33:37.214
IS THAT IT?
- GUYS, THAT'S--

33:37.320 --> 33:38.628
THERE'S PROBABLY MORE.

33:38.740 --> 33:39.832
I-I CAN'T--I CAN'T BELIEVE

33:39.940 --> 33:42.010
THAT YOU'RE ALL HERE.

33:42.120 --> 33:43.451
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT YOU ALL--

33:43.570 --> 33:45.913
THAT EACH OF YOU
THOUGHT TO COME OVER HERE.

33:46.020 --> 33:46.702
all: OF COURSE WE DID.

33:46.810 --> 33:48.778
- BUT NO, NOT OF COURSE.

33:48.880 --> 33:51.053
THIS IS AMAZING.

33:51.160 --> 33:52.127
YOU GUYS ARE AMAZING.

33:52.230 --> 33:54.607
- WE LOVE YOU.
OF COURSE WE'RE HERE.

33:54.720 --> 33:55.789
WHERE ELSE WOULD WE BE?
- WE LOVE YOU, JULES.

33:55.890 --> 33:57.471
- WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
CHEERING YOU UP THOUGH,

33:57.580 --> 33:59.263
NOT CHEERING YOU DOWN.
- YOU ARE CHEERING ME UP.

33:59.380 --> 34:01.689
- IT FEELS LIKE A CHEER-DOWN.
- [laughs] NO!

34:01.790 --> 34:02.825
- WHAT?
[upbeat music plays]

34:02.930 --> 34:05.376
- I DON'T KNOW
IF IT'S THIS WINE,

34:05.490 --> 34:06.821
BUT SUDDENLY I'M NOT FEELING
SO WELL.

34:06.940 --> 34:08.623
CAN YOU FEEL MY FOREHEAD?
- HE'S TURNING INTO THE HULK.

34:08.730 --> 34:11.312
- YOU KNOW WHAT
HE'S COMING DOWN WITH?

34:11.420 --> 34:12.489
- OH, I THINK I--
- HAVE YOU GOT A FEVER?

34:12.600 --> 34:14.522
- I THINK I MIGHT BE COMING DOWN
WITH SOME FEVER!

34:14.630 --> 34:15.972
- [squeals]
COME ON.

34:16.080 --> 34:17.877
[Burning Down the Houseplays]
- THAT MEANS I GET TO WATCH.

34:17.980 --> 34:20.119
- WE CAN'T LET HIM
DO THIS BY HIMSELF.

34:20.230 --> 34:21.879
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
- THIS IS NOT EVEN MY ERA.

34:21.990 --> 34:23.082
- TALKING HEADS
IS EVERYONE'S ERA.

34:23.190 --> 34:24.885
COME ON.
- COME ON, JULES.

34:24.990 --> 34:27.743
- LOOK AT FEVER.
JUST FOLLOW HIM.

34:27.850 --> 34:29.852
- OH, MY GOD.
[chattering]

34:29.960 --> 34:32.064
- [clucks]
THERE IT IS!

34:32.170 --> 34:33.614
- I DON'T THINK THAT'S REAL--

34:33.720 --> 34:36.302
- FEVER, GIVE US A WARNING
IF YOU NEED TO BACK UP.

34:36.410 --> 34:39.061
OH, NO, BACK UP!
- OH, I'M AFRAID, I'M AFRAID.

34:39.180 --> 34:40.750
- GET THE BACK BRACE READY.

34:40.870 --> 34:42.758
[cheering]
- [groans]

34:43.900 --> 34:45.834
- OW!
- WHOA!

34:45.940 --> 34:50.149
- WHOA!
- [groans]

34:50.260 --> 34:52.569
- JULES, COME ON.
- YEAH, GET WILD.

34:52.670 --> 34:56.709
- YEAH!
[overlapping chatter]

35:04.860 --> 35:09.206
- YOU CAN DO THIS.

35:09.310 --> 35:11.892
- THEY STILL THINK
I'M IN BOSTON.

35:12.000 --> 35:14.969
- I KNOW.

35:15.070 --> 35:19.074
- I MEAN, I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT I'M GONNA SAY TO THEM.

35:19.180 --> 35:21.831
- YOU JUST HAVE TO
TELL THEM THE TRUTH.

35:21.940 --> 35:24.829
YOU KNOW, TELL 'EM THAT
TUFTS WASN'T WHAT YOU

35:24.950 --> 35:27.976
THOUGHT IT WAS GONNA BE
AND IT'S NOT FOR YOU.

35:28.090 --> 35:30.251
AND THEY'RE GONNA UNDERSTAND.

35:35.890 --> 35:38.984
- OKAY, WELL, GIVEN EVERYTHING
I'M ABOUT TO TELL THEM,

35:39.100 --> 35:42.501
YOU PROBABLY SHOULDN'T
WAIT FOR ME.

35:42.620 --> 35:45.088
- YEAH.
I WAS THINKING THAT.

35:45.210 --> 35:49.488
- YEAH.

35:49.590 --> 35:53.242
- YOU KNOW THAT YOU CAN CALL ME
FOR ANYTHING.

35:54.840 --> 35:57.764
I MEAN IT.

36:00.150 --> 36:01.731
IF I DON'T ANSWER,

36:01.840 --> 36:06.152
I'M SURE BERTO
WILL KINDLY TAKE A MESSAGE.

36:06.260 --> 36:08.603
- [laughs]
- HE'S STILL ANSWERING MY PHONE.

36:08.710 --> 36:12.851
THERE'S JUST NO BOUNDARIES
THERE WHATSOEVER, BUT...

36:17.930 --> 36:20.922
YOU OKAY?

36:21.040 --> 36:24.794
- I'M OKAY.

36:24.900 --> 36:28.961
- FOR I'M BROKEN

36:29.080 --> 36:31.696
DOWN

36:31.810 --> 36:37.259
COMING DOWN

36:37.360 --> 36:39.601
- BYE, DREW.

36:39.710 --> 36:41.109
- BYE.

36:41.230 --> 36:45.576
- FOR MY HEART LIES

36:45.680 --> 36:49.571
FAR AND AWAY
WHERE THEY TOOK YOU DOWN

36:49.690 --> 36:55.617
LED THEM OVER
TO YOUR HOUSE

36:55.730 --> 36:57.379
- THANKS.

36:57.490 --> 37:00.550
- WHERE I'M BROKEN

37:00.660 --> 37:05.905
DOWN BY THE PEOPLE
IF THEY LET YOU BREATHE

37:06.010 --> 37:10.356
DON'T GIVE A DAMN
IF YOU STILL CAN'T SEE

37:10.460 --> 37:12.428
[engine starts]

37:12.540 --> 37:15.748
STILL MY HEART BEATS

37:15.850 --> 37:20.128
FOR YOU

37:20.230 --> 37:22.198
- ALL RIGHT, GRANDSON,
NOW LISTEN UP.

37:22.300 --> 37:24.029
- YEP.
- I AM GOING TO TEACH YOU

37:24.130 --> 37:28.271
HOW TO ROAST THE MOST PERFECT
MARSHMALLOW IN THE WORLD,

37:28.380 --> 37:33.659
AND THE SECRET IS YOU GOTTA KEEP
TURNING IT SLOWLY.

37:33.760 --> 37:35.239
- CAN YOU PUT MINE ON FOR ME?

37:36.770 --> 37:39.102
- THE MARSHMALLOW'S
GETTING ALL WARM.

37:39.220 --> 37:41.871
- OH, THANK YOU.
- YOU BET.

37:41.980 --> 37:43.356
OOH!

37:43.460 --> 37:45.564
- OH, MINE'S FALLING OFF
AND IT'S ON FIRE!

37:45.670 --> 37:46.876
- OH, OH, OH, IT'S OKAY,
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

37:46.980 --> 37:49.983
THAT'S THE WAY I LOVE THEM.

37:50.090 --> 37:50.840
- MMM.
- OKAY, LET'S TAKE IT OFF.

37:50.950 --> 37:52.326
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
- YEAH.

37:52.440 --> 37:53.464
- I DON'T REALLY
LIKE MARSHMALLOWS.

37:53.580 --> 37:55.332
THEY'RE TOO STICKY.
- THEY'RE TOO STICKY?

37:55.440 --> 37:57.055
- I JUST LIKE THE GRAHAM
CRACKERS AND CHOCOLATE.

37:57.170 --> 37:58.125
- WELL, THAT'S OKAY.

37:58.240 --> 37:59.548
THAT SOUNDS GOOD TO ME.
HERE YOU GO.

37:59.650 --> 38:01.959
- OKAY, HERE'S MY OTHER ONE.

38:02.070 --> 38:03.685
- THANKS.
- HEY, DREW.

38:03.790 --> 38:04.540
- YUM.
- HEY.

38:04.660 --> 38:06.969
- HEY, DREW.
- HOW YOU DOING?

38:07.070 --> 38:08.799
HOW ABOUT A BEER?
- HEY.

38:08.900 --> 38:11.073
HE GETS ENOUGH BEER
AT COLLEGE.

38:11.180 --> 38:12.693
YOU CAN ONLY
GET A S'MORE AT HOME.

38:12.800 --> 38:13.698
WOULD YOU GO FOR A S'MORE?
- YES, PLEASE.

38:13.800 --> 38:15.802
- ARE YA IN?
- YEAH I'M IN.

38:15.910 --> 38:18.879
- HI.
- HEY.

38:18.980 --> 38:21.357
- HOW YOU DOING?
- FINE.

38:21.470 --> 38:24.223
I...TALKED TO AMY.

38:24.330 --> 38:26.366
I DID IT, SO...

38:26.470 --> 38:28.085
- YOU OKAY?
- HERE YOU GO, GRANDSON.

38:28.200 --> 38:29.599
- THANK YOU.
- MM-HMM.

38:29.720 --> 38:30.857
- SWEETIE?

38:30.960 --> 38:33.679
- TRAVELING STREET
THAT I DID NOT KNOW

38:33.790 --> 38:37.829
WHEELS LIKE TONG
TO THE WINTER LOPE

38:37.930 --> 38:41.582
DOWN IN THE VALLEY
WHERE THE CHURCH BELLS CRY

38:41.690 --> 38:43.578
I'LL LEAD THEM OVER
TO YOUR EYES

38:43.700 --> 38:44.894
- I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE, DREW.

38:45.010 --> 38:47.387
- YEAH. ME TOO.

38:47.490 --> 38:50.698
- OH OH OH OH

38:50.810 --> 38:55.110
IAM ONE

38:55.220 --> 38:58.747
[elevator rumbling]
I AM ONE

39:34.990 --> 39:39.290
[phone rings]

39:39.410 --> 39:42.504
[phone vibrates]

39:53.140 --> 39:54.937
- JOEL?

39:55.040 --> 39:57.417
- MOM?

39:57.530 --> 39:58.906
- HEY, SWEETIE.

39:59.010 --> 40:00.568
WHAT'S UP?

40:00.670 --> 40:01.978
- I HAD A BAD DREAM.

40:02.080 --> 40:04.594
THE ELEVATOR IN THE BUILDING
MAKES THIS WEIRD NOISE.

40:04.710 --> 40:09.181
- WELL, UM, WHY DON'T YOU GO
WAKE UP YOUR DAD?

40:09.300 --> 40:10.574
- I DON'T WANNA WAKE UP DAD.

40:10.680 --> 40:12.193
CAN YOU JUST TALK TO ME?

40:12.300 --> 40:14.609
- YEAH.

40:14.720 --> 40:15.641
I CAN TALK TO YOU, SWEETIE,

40:15.750 --> 40:18.503
BUT I THINK THAT DAD
WOULD WANNA KNOW.

40:18.620 --> 40:22.067
- I JUST WANT YOU, MOM.

40:22.170 --> 40:24.559
- WELL, OKAY, I-I'M HERE.

40:24.660 --> 40:25.934
I CAN TALK TO YOU.

40:26.040 --> 40:29.794
I WILL TALK TO YOU UNTIL
YOU GO BACK TO SLEEP.

40:29.910 --> 40:30.797
- OKAY.

40:30.910 --> 40:34.004
- SO, WEIRD ELEVATOR NOISES,
HUH?

40:34.120 --> 40:35.109
- YEAH.

40:35.220 --> 40:36.596
- OF COURSE, MY MOM AND DAD'S--

40:36.710 --> 40:37.938
GRANDMA AND GRANDPA'S DOESN'T
HAVE AN ELEVATOR,

40:38.050 --> 40:40.154
BUT THEY HAVE
THOSE CREAKY OLD STAIRS.

40:40.260 --> 40:42.296
THEY USED TO WAKE ME UP
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

40:42.400 --> 40:45.608
WITH SCARY NOISES.
- REALLY?

40:45.710 --> 40:47.985
- BUT YOU KNOW
WHO WAS REALLY SCARED?

40:48.100 --> 40:51.649
YOUR UNCLE CROSBY.

40:51.750 --> 40:55.299
HE WOULD RUN INTO MY ROOM
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

40:55.410 --> 40:58.447
CONVINCED THAT SOMETHING WAS
COMING UP THE STAIRS TO GET HIM.

40:58.550 --> 41:03.271
SO ONE NIGHT,
WE SET UP A BOOBY TRAP.

41:03.390 --> 41:05.142
AFTER EVERYBODY ELSE
HAD GONE TO SLEEP,

41:05.250 --> 41:08.310
WE STRUNG DENTAL FLOSS ACROSS
THE TOP OF THE STAIRS.

41:08.430 --> 41:10.569
NOTHING WAS GONNA GET PAST US.

41:10.670 --> 41:14.538
AND YOU KNOW,
WE DID CATCH SOMETHING.

41:14.640 --> 41:16.494
YOU KNOW WHAT WE CAUGHT?

41:16.610 --> 41:19.602
YOUR GRANDPA.

41:19.710 --> 41:21.575
HE BROKE HIS NOSE.

41:21.680 --> 41:24.717
HE GROUNDED US FOR THREE WEEKS.

41:26.790 --> 41:28.951
AND, SWEETIE, YOU KNOW...

41:29.070 --> 41:32.130
IT GOT LESS SCARY.

41:32.240 --> 41:35.869
AND ALL OF THIS WILL TOO.

41:37.840 --> 41:40.764
VICTOR?

41:44.530 --> 41:45.906
GOOD NIGHT, SWEETHEART.

41:46.020 --> 41:49.877
[gentle folk song]
